OL,3,C'Forever chemicals' found in common UK
OL,4,Cfruit and vegetables
OL,6,FThe figure for strawberries was
OL,7,Ffollowed by 61% of the 109 grape
OL,8,Fsamples tested, 56% of the 121 cherry
OL,9,Fsamples, 42% of the 96 spinach samples
OL,10,Fand 38% of the 96 tomato samples.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, peaches, cucumbers,
OL,13,Fapricots and beans all saw at least
OL,14,F15% of samples containing PFAs, the
OL,15,Fanalysis showed.
OL,17,FThe PRiF report said that 56.4% of
OL,18,Fsamples tested contained a residue of
OL,19,Fpesticides they were testing, but this
OL,20,Fwas below the maximum residue level
OL,21,F(MRL) allowed in food by law.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/9
